# tests/distros/default/ — provenance

This directory backs the `default` distro served at /var/lib/distros/default/
inside Hamnix.  rc.boot's `linux` / `debian` namespace recipes bind / to that
path, so `enter linux { /usr/bin/dpkg --version }` resolves /usr/bin/dpkg to
/var/lib/distros/default/usr/bin/dpkg.

Contents fall into two layers, both staged into the cpio archive by
scripts/build_initramfs.py:

LAYER 1 — fixture tree (committed, tiny)
----------------------------------------
The directory tree IN this repo (etc/, home/, root/, sbin/, tmp/, usr/, lib/)
holds tiny smoke-test fixtures: /etc/debian_version, /etc/os-release, and
README markers in each top-level dir so the cpio carries an empty directory
shape.  This layer is enough for the namespace primitives test
(scripts/test_linux_namespace.sh) — busybox applets at /bin/* are planted
by build_initramfs.py independently from tests/u-binary/u_busybox_musl.

LAYER 2 — real Debian apt / dpkg (NOT committed; gitignored)
-------------------------------------------------------------
The real package-management binaries — apt-get, dpkg, dpkg-deb and their
shared-library closure — live in a sibling tree at
  tests/distros/debian-minbase/rootfs/
populated by tests/distros/debian-minbase/BUILD.sh (which calls debootstrap
on the host).  When build_initramfs.py is invoked with
  HAMNIX_DEFAULT_REAL_DEBIAN=1
a CURATED slice of that rootfs (apt-get, dpkg, dpkg-deb, dpkg-query, plus
ld-linux + the .so closure they need at runtime) is staged into the cpio at
/var/lib/distros/default/<rel>.  That makes
  enter linux { /usr/bin/dpkg --version }
work against the real Debian dpkg binary.

The curated slice is ~30 files / ~20 MB raw — small enough that
fs/initramfs_blob.S (~6x larger as ASM `.byte` lines) stays under the
GitHub-friendly 100 MB push limit.

To populate the rootfs/ on a fresh checkout:

    bash tests/distros/debian-minbase/BUILD.sh
    # (one-time; takes 2-5 min; needs sudo + debootstrap + ~150 MB free)

To rebuild the cpio against it:

    HAMNIX_DEFAULT_REAL_DEBIAN=1 python3 scripts/build_initramfs.py

When the rootfs/ is absent, HAMNIX_DEFAULT_REAL_DEBIAN is silently a no-op
(skip + warning); the fixture layer alone still works for the basic
namespace tests.

Source mirror: deb.debian.org/debian, release "stable" (currently trixie /
Debian 13.5 — see tests/distros/debian-minbase/rootfs/etc/debian_version
after BUILD.sh).  See tests/distros/debian-minbase/HOWTO.md and MANIFEST.txt
for the original debootstrap invocation and key-files list.
